-- Astra, Medco Energi, Semen Gresik: Indonesia Equity Preview
-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 2012-01-18T01:43:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-18/astra-medco-energi-semen-gresik-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have  unusual  moves in  Indonesian trading . Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index  rose 1.2 percent to 3,954.76.  Energy companies: Oil futures advanced 2 percent to $100.71
a barrel in New York yesterday, the first gain in four days.
Crude was recently at $101.06 a barrel.  PT Medco Energi Internasional (MEDC)  , Indonesia’s
biggest listed oil company, fell 1 percent to 2,525 rupiah and
 PT Energi Mega Persada (ENRG)  , the second largest, rose 4.9
percent to 215 rupiah.  PT Astra International (ASII)  : The company’s financing
unit, PT Astra Sedaya Finance, plans to sell 2 trillion rupiah
($218 million) of bonds to boost lending to consumers for
vehicle purchases, Astra Sedaya said in a statement published in
 Bisnis Indonesia . Astra, Indonesia’s largest automotive
retailer, gained 1.4 percent to 77,300 rupiah.  PT Semen Gresik (SMGR)  : Indonesia’s biggest cement maker
may seek a $280 million-to-$540 million loan to help fund cement
plants on Java and Sumatra islands this year, Bisnis Indonesia
reported, citing Finance Director Ahyanizzaman. Semen Gresik
gained 2.6 percent to 11,850 rupiah.  PT Timah (TINS)  : Tin futures rose 4.2 percent to $21,725
a metric ton in London yesterday, the steepest increase since
Oct. 6. Timah, Indonesia’s largest tin producer, advanced 1.2
percent to 1,730 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at   dboey@bloomberg.net  